Last month, Mark Rosenker of the National Transportation Safety Board, a national transport safety expert on CBS News, said that mobile phones were always considered to be at risk.
"Mobile phones are really a problem, not only because they could possibly create interference with navigation instruments, but because we know, according to the FCC, that they could disrupt mobile phone networks if they were used on board," Rosenker said.
An Industrial Advisory Committee established by the FAA to address the problem recommended last month that the government authorize wider use of personal electronic devices.
