The FAA began to limit the use of electronic devices in 1996 as a result of the reports on interference with navigation and communication instruments when passengers carried FM radios, the high-tech gadget then.
New line aircraft depend much more on electrical systems than previous generations of aircraft, but they are also designed to withstand electronic interference and approved by the FAA.
The airlines have allowed their passengers to use Wi-Fi at cruise altitudes for several years.
